{
  "doc_id": "60186",
  "text": "All the comparisons notwithstanding, SRCNN is still a landmark work on SR. Not only being a quintessential benchmarking method, it has also been employed in many application scenarios. In a work on face recognition [CITATION_1] , the authors got improved recognition rates when the input face images were subjected to SRCNN-Ex [CITATION_2] before the use of HMM and SVD. In [CITATION_3] , SRCNN is successfully employed to improve the quality of infrared thermography (IRT) images for object recognition. In [CITATION_4] , the authors compare the performance of SRCNN with another SR method [CITATION_5] in improving the resolution of lensless blood cell counting images; SRCNN is reported to have 9.5% better results. The method in [CITATION_6] can process sketch images of any resolution and employs CNNs to auto-clean rough raster sketch drawings. The authors of [CITATION_7] apply CNN to Light-Field (LF) images -hence the name LFCNN -to upsample both the angular and spatial resolutions.",
